LABEL: A rdfs:label
definition: A definition SPLIT=|

LABEL: DNA vaccine expresses protein antigen
definition: An 'expresses' relation that specifies a relation between a DNA vaccine and a  protein antigen to be expressed by the DNA vaccine.

LABEL: has subunit vaccine protective antigen
definition: A 'has subunit vaccine antigen' relation that indicates the antigen is protective.

LABEL: has subunit vaccine antigen
definition: A type of 'has vaccine antigen' relation that is specifically for vaccine protective protein antigen used in subunit vaccine development

LABEL: has vaccine protective antigen
definition: A type of 'has vaccine antigen' relation that is specifically for vaccine protective antigen component

LABEL: has DNA vaccine antigen gene
definition: A 'has vaccine component' relation that specifies a gene inserted to DNA vaccine plasmid for development of a particular DNA vaccine, and this gene encodes for a protein antigen.

LABEL: has DNA vaccine plasmid
definition: A 'has vaccine component' relation that specifies the plasmid used for development of a particular DNA vaccine.

LABEL: has vaccine adjuvant
definition: A type of 'has vaccine component' relation that is specifically for vaccine adjuvant component

LABEL: has vaccine conjugate protein
definition: A type of 'has vaccine component' relation that specifies a vaccine conjugate protein for a specific vaccine

LABEL: has vaccine preservative
definition: A 'has vaccine component' relation that is specifically used for vaccine preservative

LABEL: has vaccine vector
definition: A type of 'has vaccine component' relation that is specifically for vaccine vector component

LABEL: has bacterial vaccine vector
definition: A type of 'has vaccine vector' relation that specifies a bacterial vaccine vector

LABEL: has viral vaccine vector
definition: A type of 'has vaccine vector' that is specifically for viral vaccine vector

LABEL: blocks transmission of pathogen via vaccine
Parent: immunizes against pathogen|capable of blocking transmission (of life cycle)
definition: A relation between a vaccine and a parasite where the vaccine immunizes against some parasite such that the parasite is blocked transmitting to additional hosts or vectors.

LABEL: capable of blocking transmission (of life cycle)
definition: A relation between a material entity  and a parasite where the material entity causes some process against some parasite such that transmitting to additional hosts or vectors.

LABEL: has boost vaccine
definition: An object property that represents a relation between a vaccine with a prime-boost schedule and a vaccine used for boost.

LABEL: has gene mutation
definition: An object property that represents an organism has a mutation of a specific gene from the organism genome.

LABEL: has molecular receptor
definition: An object property that represents a relation between a material entity and a molecular entitiy that serves as the molecular receptor to the material entity.
example of usage: A vaccine adjuvant T-vant has molecular receptor of TLR4. Reference: https://vac.niaid.nih.gov/view?id=61.

LABEL: has prime vaccine
definition: An object property that represents a relation between a vaccine with a prime-boost schedule and a vaccine used for priming.

LABEL: has vaccine allergen
definition: An object property that specifies a relation between a vaccine and a vaccine allergen

LABEL: has vaccine antigen
definition: An object property that specifies a vaccine antigen
editor note: This relation only works for those vaccine antigen that is physically part of a vaccine preparation. It does not include those antigens that are not part of vaccine. For example, a protein antigen expressed in a DNA vaccine is not a part of vaccine pe ser. In this case, the vaccine expresses the protein, but the gene is part of the vaccine, not the protein. For the case, we can use the relation 'DNA vaccine expresses protein antigen' under the relation 'expresses'.

LABEL: has vaccine component
definition: An object property that defines a relation between a vaccine and its component

LABEL: has vaccine contraindication
definition: A relation that specifies contraindication of a vaccine.
editor note: This relation may be replaced by has_vaccine_allergen. We need to determine if any vaccine contraindicator is not a vaccine allergen.

LABEL: has vaccine virmugen
definition: An object property that specifies a relation between a vaccine and a vaccine virmugen.
editor note:
This is a shortcut relation.
Domain: vaccine
Range: a gene

Shortcut:
is_specified_output_of some 
('preparation of gene mutant vaccine' and (has_specified_input some gene))

LABEL: has vaccinee
definition: An object property that specifies a relation between a vaccine and its vaccinee

LABEL: immunizes against disease
alternative label: immunization against disease|vaccine immunization against disease
definition:
A shortcut relation that is equivalent to:
'processed material' and (is_specified_output_of some 'vaccine preparation') and ('has function' some ('vaccine function' and ('is realized by' only ('vaccine immunization' and (realizes some ('vaccine host role' and (role_of some 'organism' and has_disposition some disease)))))))).
The domain of this relation is a vaccine.
The range of this relation is a disease.

LABEL: immunizes against pathogen
alternative label: immunization against pathogen|vaccine immunization against pathogen|immunizes against microbe
definition:
A shortcut relation that is equivalent to:
processed material and (is_specified_output_of some vaccine preparation) and (has function some (vaccine function and (is realized by only (vaccine immunization and (realizes some ('immunization target role' and (role_of some 'pathogen'))))))))

The domain of this relation is a vaccine.
The range of this relation is a pathogen (a bacterium, a virus, a fungus, and a parasite)
Ranges: organism and 'has role' some 'pathogen role'

LABEL: immunizes recipient
alternative label: immunization for host|vaccine immunization for recipient|immunizes host|vaccine immunization for host|immunization for recipient
definition:
A shortcut relation that is equivalent to:
'processed material' and (is_specified_output_of some 'vaccine preparation') and ('has function' some ('vaccine function' and ('is realized by' only ('vaccine immunization' and (realizes some ('vaccine recipient role' and (role_of some 'organism')))))))).
The domain of this relation is a vaccine.
The range of this relation is a organism.
term editor: Asiyah Yu Lin|Oliver He|Barry Smith|Jie Zheng|Anna Maria Masci

LABEL: induced by vaccination of
definition: An object property that specifies a process that is induced by vaccination of a vaccine

LABEL: induces immune profile
definition: An object property that represents a relation between a material entity (such as vaccine or vaccine adjuvant) and an immune profile where the material entity can induce the immune profile in a host.

LABEL: infection_of
definition: A relation between a disorder and an infectious pathogen.
term editor: Oliver He|Allen Xiang|Melanie Courtot|Bjoern Peters|Alan Ruttenburg
editor note:
The relation 'infection_of' is introduced to represent an infection caused by an infectious pathogen. A pathogen infection is a disorder. Since the number of pathogens is large, there are numerous infections. To make the description of a specific infection simple, the shortcut term 'infection_of' is defined: 
infection_of X = infection and has_part some (organism X and has_disposition some infectious disposition)

LABEL: is_distributed_by
definition: A relation that specifies a company that distributes a product (e.g., vaccine). The company is very likely not the manufacturer of the product.

LABEL: up-expressed as immune signature of
definition: An object property that represents a relation between a material entity and biological process

LABEL: vaccinated in route
definition: An object property that specifies a relation between a vaccine and a vaccinate route

LABEL: vaccine immunity response transferrable to organism
definition: A relation between a vaccine X and organism Y where the vaccine X generates an immune response in a vaccinated organism and the immune product (e.g., antibody) can be transferred to the organism Y

LABEL: vaccine organism has mutation
definition: An object property that represents a mutational relation between a vaccine organism and another material (e.g., gene or protein). the mutated material initially exists in the original wildtype organism.

LABEL: vaccine organism secretes
definition: An object property that indicates a secretion of a material (e.g., protein) from a vaccine organism.

LABEL: has vaccine organism with quality
definition:
A shortcut relation that is equivalent to:
('vaccine') and ('has component' some ('vaccine organism' and 'has quality' some 'organismal quality').
The domain of this relation is a vaccine.
The range of this relation is a organismal quality.

LABEL: test in laboratory model
definition:
A shortcut relation that is equivalent to:
('vaccine' and 'has function' some ('vaccine function' and ('is realized by' some ('vaccine immunization' and 'has participant' some ('organism' and 'has role' some 'laboratory animal model role'))))).
The domain of this relation is a vaccine.
The range of this relation is a organism.
